100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 19, 1925, British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin announced plans to address the growing economic challenges facing the nation, emphasizing the need for stability. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes, charged with teaching evolution in Tennessee, continued to draw national attention, spotlighting the clash between modern science and traditional beliefs. Meanwhile, in Germany, the political landscape remained tense as the government struggled to manage the repercussions of the Treaty of Versailles.
